If it be true , then , O Sossius Senecio , [*] as Simonides says , [*] that Ilium
is not wroth with the Corinthians
for coming up against her with the Achaeans , because the Trojans also had Glaucus , who sprang from Corinth , as a zealous ally , so it is likely that neither Romans nor Greeks will quarrel with the Academy , since they fare alike in this treatise containing the lives of Dion and Brutus ,
